==English==
===Etymology===
From [[parallax]] of one arc [[second]]

===Noun===
'''parsec''' (''plural'' '''parsecs''')

# A unit of [[length]] used to measure the [[distance]]s of [[star|stars]] from the [[Earth]], defined as the distance from the Earth of a [[star]] that has a [[parallax]] of 1 [[arcsecond]]

  1 Parsec = 3.08568025 × 10<sup>16</sup> meters = 3.2616 light-years

